# Client React Conventions

## Stack

- React 19 + TypeScript + Vite (ESM, bundler module resolution)
- react-chessboard v5 — all config goes through `options` prop, NOT top-level props
- Socket.IO client singleton in `src/socket.ts`
- CSS Modules (`*.module.css`) for component styles

## react-chessboard v5 API

```tsx
<Chessboard options={{ position, onPieceDrop, boardOrientation, squareStyles, ... }} />
```

Key options: `position`, `onPieceDrop`, `onPieceDrag`, `onPieceClick`, `onSquareClick`, `squareStyles`, `boardOrientation`, `darkSquareStyle`, `lightSquareStyle`, `darkSquareNotationStyle`, `lightSquareNotationStyle`, `alphaNotationStyle`, `numericNotationStyle`

## Patterns

- Board sizing is CSS-driven: constrain the `.board` container, the component fills it
- Legal move highlighting: compute via `game.moves({ square, verbose: true })`, render via `squareStyles`
- Reconnection: `roomId` persisted in localStorage, auto-rejoin on mount and on `socket.io.reconnect`

## Testing

- Tests use Vitest (configured in `vite.config.ts` with `jsdom` environment)
- Run with `npm test` (vitest run)

### Test structure

- `legalMoves.test.ts` — Legal move highlighting logic: pawn/knight/queen moves, capture vs dot classification, pinned pieces, en passant, castling, null selection
- `gameLogic.test.ts` — Client game helpers: turn detection, isMyTurn logic, promotion detection, board orientation, player bar layout, time formatting, move list pairing
- `reconnection.test.ts` — localStorage reconnection patterns: store/clear/read room ID and player name, rejoin detection logic, stale room cleanup on failed rejoin

### Key rules

- Don't use `localStorage` directly in tests (jsdom doesn't fully support it); use a simple Map-based store that mirrors the same get/set/remove patterns
- Test pure logic extracted from components, not component rendering (no React Testing Library needed for current tests)
